{
  "texts": [
    "The k-th Betti number is defined as the group rank of the k-th homology.",
    "In group theory, rank refers to the concept of independence, it is closely related to the concept of rank from linear algebra, and it represents dimensionality (Hatcher 2002).",
    "In general, the Betti numbers can be quite difficult to compute, but fortunately, there are some settings where the calculations are straightforward.",
    "The k-th homology is much more convenient to work with when we restrict ourselves to simplicial complexes, which are structures built upon discrete sets.",
    "This is the natural domain for data-driven and machine-learning applications."
  ]
}